        <abstract>
            <p>Believes the British and Norwegian species of red grouse are merely strongly marked varieties of the same species.</p>
            <p>Writes of the effect of importing a few brace of a wilder breed of grouse into Argyleshire and of their change in territory since 1846.</p>
            <p>His explanation of game becoming "wilder": he thinks it is due to a difference in their enemies – man replacing hawks leads to flight replacing cowering.</p>
        </abstract>
